I"<<p><img src="/assets/img/rust/redox.jpg" alt="Redox OS - A system written in Rust - Installation and Concepts" /></p>

<p><a href="https://redox-os.org/">Redox</a> is a microkernel operating system similar to <a href="https://en.terminalroot.com.br/the-13-best-shell-for-your-linux-or-unix/">Unix</a> written in the Rust programming language, which has a strong focus on security, stability and high performance.</p>

<p>Redox is inspired by previous kernels and operating systems, such as SeL4, MINIX, Plan 9 and BSD. It is similar to <a href="https://en.terminalroot.com.br/gnu-autotools-ultimate-tutorial-for-beginners/">GNU</a> and <a href="https://en.terminalroot.com.br/openbsd-dual-boot-with-linux-single-partition/">BSD</a>, but it is written in Rust. It is free and open source software distributed under an MIT license.</p>

<p>Redox was created by Jeremy Soller and was first published on April 20, 2015 on <a href="github.com/terroo">GitHub</a>.</p>

